<h1><%= chapter %>. The Web server</h1>
<p>The default built-in web server is multi-threaded, with very good response time. You
can also use one of the other servers : <CODE>Karrigell_HTTPServer.py</CODE> (mono-thread), 
<CODE>Karrigell_AsyncHTTPServer.py</CODE> (asynchronous), 
<CODE>Karrigell_multiprocess.py</CODE> (multi process, requires the PyProcessing module)

<p>

<p>
The command line to start the built-in web server is :
<div class="verbatim"><pre>
<code>python Karrigell.py [ServerConfigDirectory]</code>
</pre>
</div>
<p>The option <code>ServerConfigDirectory</code> is explained in section 
<%= make_link("configuration","configuration") %>


